<paragraph blockId="11.[192,1440,1187,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
One female housed in the USNM collection and with the following label data seems to have been temporarily misplaced: Borinquen, 
<collectingCountry box="[632,781,1251,1275]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
, 
<date box="[792,923,1251,1275]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" value="1944-06-18">18.vi.1944</date>
, plane 5978, #1918, lo. no. 44 19590. This specimen was studied by the senior author (JAG) in 1999 while visiting the collection. The reddish-brown color on metasomal tergum I is more extensively present in the basal area (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dewitz" authorityYear="1881" box="[1132,1258,1316,1339]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Coelioxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis box="[1132,1258,1316,1339]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">C. spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this coloration occurs only laterally), the apical process of metasomal sternum VI is short (versus elongate in 
<emphasis box="[1309,1440,1348,1371]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dewitz" authorityYear="1881" box="[1309,1433,1348,1371]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Coelioxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">C. spinosa</taxonomicName>
;
</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[192,297,1379,1403]" captionStart="Figure 14-15" captionStartId="8.[192,276,886,908]" captionTargetBox="[195,1443,191,864]" captionTargetId="figure-248@8.[195,1443,191,864]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 14-15. Coelioxys species. 14) C. abdominalis Guérin-Méneville. 15) C. spinosa Dewitz holotype, and sixth metasomal tergum (magnified): A) male; B) female. Photo by Stephanie Krause." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169672/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Fig. 15B</figureCitation>
), and the apical margin of tergum VI is tridentate. Drawings of the female’s scutellum, axillae and apex of the metasoma were published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Genaro, J. A." box="[737,910,1411,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="951 - 959" refId="ref13078" refString="Genaro, J. A. 2001. Especies nuevas de abejas de Cuba y la Espanola (Hymenoptera: Colletidae, Megachilidae, Apidae). Revista de Biologia Tropical 49: 951 - 959." type="journal article" year="2001">Genaro (2001)</bibRefCitation>
as erroneously pertaining to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dewitz" authorityYear="1881" box="[1262,1387,1412,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Coelioxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis box="[1262,1387,1412,1435]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">C. spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
